.TH CMT_ARCHITECTURE 3 "CMT" "CMT_ARCHITECTURE" "CPU Architecture Detection"

.SH NAME
CMT_ARCHITECTURE \- Detect CPU and compiler target bit-width

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #define INCL__ARCHITECTURE
.br
.B #include <CMT/CMT.H>

.SH FILES
CMT/ENVIRONMENTS/ARCHITECTURE.H

.SH DESCRIPTION
This header provides macros for determining the target system's architecture bit-width as detected by the compiler.

.SH MACROS
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_64_BIT__
Defined if the system is 64-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_32_BIT__
Defined if the system is 32-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_31_BIT__
Defined if the system also supports 31-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_16_BIT__
Defined if the system is 16-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_8_BIT__
Defined if the system is 8-bit.
.TP
.B __SYSTEM_BIT__
Macro indicating the system bit-width.

.SH EXTENDED INTEGER SIZES
.TP
.B __HAS_128_BIT__
Defined if the system supports 128-bit integers.
.TP
.B __HAS_64_BIT__
Defined if the system supports 64-bit integers (for 32/16-bit systems).

.SH VECTOR REGISTER SIZES
.TP
.B __HAS_512_BIT_VECTOR__
Defined if the system supports 512-bit vector registers.
.TP
.B __HAS_256_BIT_VECTOR__
Defined if the system supports 256-bit vector registers.
.TP
.B __HAS_128_BIT_VECTOR__
Defined if the system supports 128-bit vector registers.

.SH DETAILS
These macros allow compile-time selection of behavior depending on the underlying CPU or compiler-targeted architecture.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B CMT_CPU(3),
.B CMT(3)

